news.title: Nvidia CEO Huang says AI has to do '100 times more' computation now than when ChatGPT was released
news.summary: Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang spoke with CNBC's Jon Fortt following the chipmaker's quarterly earnings report on Wednesday. Huang: "I think we're on the right track. We're going to continue to make progress"

news.title: Stripe's valuation climbs to $91.5 billion in secondary stock offer
news.summary: Stripe announced a tender offer on Thursday that values the company at close to its peak valuation from 2021. Stripe is a social payments company that was founded in 2007.

news.title: WBD adds 6.4 million Max subscribers, forecasts 150 million subs by end of 2026
news.summary: Warner Bros. Discovery says it added 6.4 million global streaming subscribers in the fourth quarter. That's a total of 116.9 million subscribers.

news.title: Trump threatens to slap 25% tariffs on EU, says bloc was always meant to hurt the U.S.
news.summary: U.S. President Donald Trump threatened to impose 25% tariffs on imports from the European Union. Trump claimed that the bloc was formed "to screw" the U.S., claiming that it was formed to "screw" him.

news.title: Amazon touts its first quantum computing chip a week after Microsoft's unveiling
news.summary: The chip will help the online retailer build highly efficient hardware systems, Amazon says. The chip is the first of its kind and will be used for quantum computing.

news.title: Swiss Re expects LA wildfire costs to come in at under $700 million
news.summary: Swiss Re said its LA wildfire losses would come in under $700 million. Swiss Re said it had no plans to “pull back” from California.

news.title: Rolls-Royce, whose stock-market performance is close to Nvidia’s, rallies again
news.summary: Rolls-Royce is one of the hottest stocks in Europe over the last two years. The engine maker beat analyst expectations and set medium term guidance that points to continued growth.
